 ?',NULL,NULL,0,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(124,3,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Wie können wir eine weltweite Medizinische Versorgung (Krankenversicherung) herstellen?',NULL,NULL,0,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(125,2,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Wie kann Wasser verwenden ohne eine Krankheit in die Bevölkerung zu bringen und gleichzeitig einen fruchtbaren Boden zum Anbau von Lebensmitteln zu erschaffen ',NULL,NULL,0,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(126,2,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Wie kann Wasser verwenden ohne eine Krankheit in die Bevölkerung zu bringen und gleichzeitig einen fruchtbaren Boden zum Anbau von Lebensmitteln zu erschaffen ',NULL,NULL,0,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(127,2,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Wie kann Wasser verwenden ohne eine Krankheit in die Bevölkerung zu bringen und gleichzeitig einen fruchtbaren Boden zum Anbau von Lebensmitteln zu erschaffen ',NULL,NULL,0,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(128,2,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Wie kann Wasser verwenden ohne eine Krankheit in die Bevölkerung zu bringen und gleichzeitig einen fruchtbaren Boden zum Anbau von Lebensmitteln zu erschaffen ',NULL,NULL,0,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(129,17,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Wie verbessere ich die Kommunikation bei Partnerschaften? ',NULL,NULL,0,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(130,3,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'wie können wir cannabis für medizinische gründe legalisieren.',NULL,NULL,0,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(131,11,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,7,'How can we stop buildings over-heating on a hot day?','The external surface  of buildings can absorb heat and transfer it inside the building. This increase in internal temperature requires additional methods to keep the inside cool - better to avoid heating the building in the first place. Your Team has been asked to create a method (using biomimicry) to reduce the heat gain in external building walls.','You might like to think consider different approaches: changing the structure of building materials, creating a new coating for existing buildings, or rethinking the heat absoprtion properties of building materials. Also think about the location of the building - which parts warm the most and when?',0,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(132,9,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,7,'What if buildings cooled themselves without energy from fossil fuels?','When it\'s hot outside, buildings require a lot of external energy to cool them. With raising temperatures and more extreme weather events, this demand for energy will increase unless we can design buildings more smartly. Is there a building you use which needs improving? Your Team has been asked to design a building (using biomimicry) that keeps cool in summer and warm in winter, and does so with minimal energy use.  ','You can choose to work on a whole building design, or select one specific element to focus on. You might like to consider the effect of the local climate on the needs of your building as well as other considerations such as locally available building materials, and the needs of the people using the building.',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(133,12,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,7,'Can we create clothing which does not harm the planet?','Producing clothes uses energy and resources, and after use most clothes end up in landfull and cannot biodegrade. Can we grow materials for clothing in the same way nature grows its own \'clothing\'? You Team has been asked (using biomimicry) to suggest new materials for creating sustainable clothing.','You might like to consider where the clothes will be worn and for what purpose. Will they need to be waterproof or address any other environmental conditions? Will they need to provide protection e.g. against spills, or are they just for \'looks\'?',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(134,3,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,7,'How can we design a building that keeps people healthy whilst minimizing the ecological impact of the building?','Nature can teach us a lot about lighting, air quality, temperature control and insulation and how it optimizes these Functions, rather than maximizes one. Your team has been asked to design a building (using biomimicry) that optimizes users’ wellbeing indoors whilst minimizing the ecological footprint of the building.','You might like to consider adapting an existing building or creating a completely new one. Either way, who is using the building and for what purpose? Will users be in the building for work, meetings or it is it a residential building? Consider the local environment and availability of materials.',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(135,11,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,7,'How can we create more efficient ways to travel where we need to go?','Our current transport system often priortises cars over people. It is fossil-fuel based and has a large impact on ecosystems and the climate crisis. In nature, organisms use ways of transportation that are efficient and demand-based. Swarms and colonies, for example, use communication mechanisms to share the energy consumed by a collective movement process. Your Team as been asked (unsing biomimicry) to design a more efficient system for organising how people move around an urban city.','This is a big Challenge, and you might like to focus on a small part of one town. How might you reorgainse bus services or even taxis to be multi-occupancy? You will need to think about the whole system of transport and perhaps even the infrastructure of the town e.g. roads, parking, movement of cars and pedestrians. ',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(136,11,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,7,'Can we create building materials which reduce carbon emissions?','Globally, the cement industry alone emits 2.8bn tonnes of carbon dioxide each year. Nature has a different approach, and often reduces carbon in the atmosphere during it’s a building. Your Team has been asked (using biomimcry) to create a new building material which does not emit carbon during manufacture.','You might like to be really specific on the type of building material you wish to create - the humble house brick? What will your new building material need to do - join together to create walls, bear weight, etc? This might require an bit of initial research.',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(137,12,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,7,'What if our clothes grew with us?','Fashion production makes up 10% of humanity\'s carbon emissions, and 85% of all textiles end up in landfill.  What if we didn\'t need to keep buying clothes? What if they grew with us and repaired themselves? Your Team has been asked (using biomimcry) to create a new textile which can adapt over time (grow, repair).','You might like to consider the context in which the material will be used. Will it need to protect against the weather, be used to keep the wearer safe from spills, or simply to look good?',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(138,11,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,7,'How can buildings adapt to changing sea levels and increased flooding?','Floods are a normal part of life for many people in Bangladesh. But with global heating and sea level rise, they are becoming more common. How can villagers continue to live in their houses and adapt to this change? Your Team has been asked (using biomimicry) to develop a new low cost family house which can adapt to changing water levels.','You might like to think about the specific location of the village and research how often flooding takes place and how deep the flood water might be. Also, during the flooding how can families access their houses?',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(139,12,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,7,'How to keep kitchen surfaces clean and hygienic?','We spend a lot of money each year buying chemicals to keep surfaces in the home clean and hygienic. Is there a better way to maintain hygiene with less chemicals? Your Team has been asked (using biommicry) to create a new kitchen surface which remains hygienic, only using water to remove bacteria. ','You might like to consider what the surface is made of, not just how it works. ',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(140,2,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,7,'How to grow food in cities?','Cities used to produce much of their food locally, but now rely on vast food chains to stay provisioned. Your Team has been asked (using biommicry) to seek solutions that foster the expansion of urban agriculture in a way that significantly increases the proportion of locally produced/grown foods in urban diets. ','You might like to consider you design an urban food production system that functions like nature and without the negative side effects of conventional agriculture (soil depletion, pollution, biodiversity loss)? Also, who will grow the food - staff or local people? How much time will they need to commit?',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(141,3,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,7,'How to make glue that doesn\'t kill you?','From your tennis shoes to your desk at school, adhesives or glues are a major part of our world. Your Team has been asked (using biomimicry) to find non-toxic and high-performance solutions would have wide application in human products.','You might like to consider where your glue will be used - what type of product will be used in? Will the glue need to be permanent or temporary? Understanding the performance requirements will help refine this Challenge to be more manageable.',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(142,12,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,7,'How to sleep warm and waste free?','We want to keep warm when we go to sleep, but also not damage the planet we depend upon. Your Team has been asked (using biommicry) by a mattress manufacturing company to design a mattress which is inspired by nature to help keep customers warm and eliminate waste.','You might like to consider where the mattress will be used i.e. in cold or hot climates? Also, how can the mattress be re-used after use or designed to become a resource for a new product.',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(143,8,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,7,'How does my business get noticed?','A new company is about to open up a flagship store that will change the understanding of retail in its sector. A huge amount of budget has been absorbed by the design and building of the new store. Now it is time to find smart ways of generating awareness about this unique place. Your Team has been asked (using biomimicry) to create an eye-cathing visual display outside the new flagship store. The display must mirror the company\'s ethos of being the most sustainable business on the planet.','You might like to consider all the elements involved in creating a visual display - materials, colours, lights, etc. Do you want to focus on one element or the whole thing? You might start exploring the whole visual display design and then narrow on a specific Design Solution later.',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(144,8,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,7,'How does nature relax?','Your organisation is a leader in innovations related to implementing biomimicry into sustainability projects. The business has been growing quickly and everyone is working hard. The CEO has asked you and your team, members of the HR Department, to take on a challenge: “While there are many ways that humans seem to be distinct from other species, one thing I notice in particular is that other species don’t appear to be overworked, stressed, and inefficient (except perhaps in severely degraded habitats). Yet, we suffer from those conditions, and I see it taking a toll on everyone and on our organisation.” She challenges you to develop new bio-inspired working policies for the organisation, to ensure that individuals and the whole will thrive.','You might like to consider finding a local business (or your school) to focus your thinking - having some real-life test subjects will he helpful. ',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(145,9,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,7,'How do I find likeminded people to collaborate with?','With the increased need for materials that don\'t use \"heat, beat, and treat\" manufacturing processes, the field of green chemistry is taking off. Professonals in the field want to build a network of strategic partners with expertise in green chemistry. They are looking for inspiration from nature on how to find one another and develop the network. Your Team has been asked (using biomimicry) to create a solution.','You might like to think about how to communicate messages and information, how to send signals.',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(146,12,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,7,'How to make better choices quickly?','\'\'Choice fatigue\' is one result of our consumer based society. Research indicates that more choice and too many options can lead to stress, anxiety and uncertainty. Other organisms make choices all the time but in different ways to humans. Your Team has been asked (using biomimicry) to suggest better ways to make choices based on strategies from nature.','You might like to focus on a specific type of product e.g. mobile phones or retail location e.g. cloths shop; or you could think about a particular choice people have to make e.g. what to watch on Netflix or what to wear.',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL);
